;; minidrama.app.edn — KOTOBA Mesh application manifest for the minidrama
;; actor's ON-MESH surface (kenchi-valuation 同型, see ../docs and
;; ADR-2607071500 in the superproject). murakumo.app.edn references this as a
;; fleet app; `kotoba app deploy mesh/minidrama.app.edn --publish --url
;; http://node:8080` compiles each :src to a CID and announces the
;; triggers/routes to a node.
;;
;; SPLIT OF DUTIES (kenchi §6 と同じ分業):
;;   - The DRAMA PIPELINE (DramaLLM proposal → DramaGovernor → ledger →
;;     generate/assemble → aozora publish) runs OFF-MESH on the JVM actor
;;     (minidrama.operation / minidrama.publisher / minidrama.announce) —
;;     LLM 呼び出し・動画生成・PDS 認証はこの mesh guest では行わない。
;;   - THESE on-mesh components only PUBLISH the actor's identity/liveness and
;;     SERVE its profile:
;;       drama-profile    on-http  GET /minidrama/profile → the actor's
;;                                 identity record (handle / did / registry)
;;       drama-heartbeat  on-tick  assert resident-liveness datoms so the
;;                                 fleet's Datom log carries an as-of history
;;                                 that the actor is resident and reachable
;;   This gives the actor 常駐 (LaunchAgent-hosted kotoba-server), p2p (the
;;   gossipsub lattice places and re-places it), and HTTP reachability without
;;   moving any governor-gated capability on-mesh.
{:kotoba.app/name    "minidrama"
 :kotoba.app/version "0.1.0"
 :kotoba.app/components
 [{:name     "drama-profile"
   :src      "drama_profile.clj"            ; Clojure default → compiled to CID
   :scale    1
   :triggers [{:type :http :route "/minidrama/profile"}]
   :requires #{:cap/kqe}}

  {:name     "drama-heartbeat"
   :src      "drama_heartbeat.clj"
   :scale    1
   :triggers [{:type :tick :every "1h"}]    ; periodic liveness assert
   :requires #{:cap/kqe}}]

 ;; Place on the JP edge tribe (same class murakumo's other mesh apps use).
 :kotoba.app/placement {:spread  :zone
                        :require {:tier "edge"}}}
